description:
Harsh Realm was a series from writer James Hudnall and Andrew Paquette. Set in the future where virtual realities exist, the Harsh Realm was a unsupervised virtual reality where anything goes. Private Investigator Dexter Green is hired to enter the Harsh Realm to look for the missing son of a wealthy family. 
 
The series was loosely adapted into the short-lived FOX  television series Harsh Realm in 1999. 
 
Collected Editions: 

  • Harsh Realm (1999)
name: Harsh Realm

description:
Hasbro Transformers Collectors' Club The Official Magazine is published by the official fan club license-holder Fun Publications on a bi-monthly basis. The magazine includes stories, interviews, previews of upcoming toys, fan art, and comics. The comic are normally a 6-part story arc and are broken up and published throughout the year.

Note: The first 12 issues did not have covers and were The Official Newsletter instead of The Official Magazine.

Collected Editions

  • Transformers: Cybertron: Balancing Act (Comics from Issues 1-12)
  • Transformers Collectors' Club Magazine Collected Edition Volume 1 (Issues 1-6) *Listed as Jan 2013 Mailing Date
name: Hasbro Transformers Collectors' Club
